>    X[i+1] = Hash(MyMessage:X[i])
  [ ... ]
> This recurrence will eventually repeat with some cycle length. By the
> Birthday property, the expected cycle length is sqrt(2^N), where N is
> the number of bits in the hash function.

No. The function f(x) = hash(blah+x), mapping hash values to hash 
values, ``should'' behave like a permutation, and for most hash 
functions it _is_ a permutation. Maybe there's a way to do a birthday
attack without much memory, but this isn't it.

---Dan
